==Old English==
===Etymology===
Genitive singular form of [[þæt]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ðæs/}}

===Demonstrative Pronoun===
'''þæs''' ''m'' or ''n''
# genitive singular form of [[se#Old English|se]]
# genitive singular form of [[þæt]]

===Adverb===
'''þæs'''
# [[afterwards]]
# [[regarding]], in respect of, on that account, [[therefore]], [[so]]
#:''Sy him ðæs a wuldor'': May glory be his forever because of that.  (Ælfric's ''Lives of Saints'')

===Conjunction===
'''þæs'''
# [[as]], [[because]]
# [[after]]

